===== install/v0.1/install_prompt.md
     1	Use this prompt to install and initialize AOPMem v0.1 for the current
     2	repository.
     3	
     4	````text
     5	You are installing AOPMem v0.1 into the user's current host and initializing
     6	it for the current repository.
     7	
     8	Important rules:
     9	
    10	- Do the full install and workspace init flow.
    11	- Stay inside user-level install only.
    12	- Detect technical facts silently.
    13	- Do not ask the user about things you can detect yourself.
    14	- Do not ask any irrelevant technical questionnaire.
    15	- Ask only the 5 semantic questions listed below.
    16	- No final confirmation ceremony.
    17	- If the managed AOPMem block already exists, update only that block.
    18	- If the managed block is damaged, stop with an explicit error.
    19	- Do not build from source during user install when a matching binary artifact
    20	  exists.
    21	- If the matching binary artifact is missing, fail fast with:
    22	  binary artifact missing for current platform.
    23	- Do not create `.aopmem` in the target repository.
    24	- Do not use WSL as the Windows install path.
    25	
    26	Supported platforms:
    27	
    28	- macOS Apple Silicon:
    29	  - detect macOS + arm64 silently.
    30	  - install from `dist/aopmem-darwin-arm64/aopmem`.
    31	  - install to `~/.aopmem/bin/aopmem`.
    32	- Windows x64 native PowerShell:
    33	  - detect Windows + x64 silently.
    34	  - install from `dist\aopmem-windows-x86_64\aopmem.exe`.
    35	  - install to `%USERPROFILE%\.aopmem\bin\aopmem.exe`.
    36	  - use PowerShell commands only.
    37	  - use backslashes in Windows path examples.
    38	
    39	Unsupported platforms:
    40	
    41	- Linux is unsupported in v0.1 rc2.
    42	- Windows ARM is unsupported in v0.1 rc2.
    43	- Intel macOS is unsupported in v0.1 rc2.
    44	
    45	Silent technical detection:
    46	
    47	- current OS and architecture
    48	- current repo root
    49	- current agent environment and instruction file
    50	- existing managed AOPMem block
    51	- whether AOPMem is already installed globally
    52	- workspace key
    53	- backend path under the user-level AOPMem home
    54	- whether .understand.docs already exists
    55	
    56	Install flow:
    57	
    58	1. Check whether AOPMem is already installed globally.
    59	2. Select the matching prebuilt binary for the current platform.
    60	3. If the matching binary artifact is missing, fail fast.
    61	4. If AOPMem is missing, install the AOPMem CLI into the user-level bin dir.
    62	5. Create and verify the required global directories under the user-level
    63	   AOPMem home.
    64	6. Create or reuse the workspace for the current repository under
    65	   <AOPMem home>/workspaces/<workspace-key>.
    66	7. Ask whether to enable Understand Anything.
    67	8. If enabled, do best-effort local setup and create .understand.docs.
    68	9. Ask whether to enable Codebase Memory MCP.
    69	10. If enabled, do best-effort local setup.
    70	11. Ask the semantic project onboarding questions.
    71	12. Seed the collected semantic answers into AOPMem.
    72	13. Seed the required default kernel/contracts/gates data.
    73	14. Insert or update the managed AOPMem block in the current instruction file.
    74	15. Initialize local audit snapshots.
    75	16. Run `aopmem doctor`.
    76	17. Run the first recall bundle.
    77	
    78	macOS Apple Silicon install commands:
    79	
    80	```sh
    81	mkdir -p "$HOME/.aopmem/bin"
    82	test -s "dist/aopmem-darwin-arm64/aopmem" || {
    83	  echo "binary artifact missing for current platform" >&2
    84	  exit 1
    85	}
    86	cp "dist/aopmem-darwin-arm64/aopmem" "$HOME/.aopmem/bin/aopmem"
    87	chmod 755 "$HOME/.aopmem/bin/aopmem"
    88	"$HOME/.aopmem/bin/aopmem" --version
    89	```
    90	
    91	Windows x64 native PowerShell install commands:
    92	
    93	```powershell
    94	$InstallDir = "$env:USERPROFILE\.aopmem\bin"
    95	New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force $InstallDir | Out-Null
    96	if (-not (Test-Path ".\dist\aopmem-windows-x86_64\aopmem.exe")) {
    97	  Write-Error "binary artifact missing for current platform"
    98	  exit 1
    99	}
   100	Copy-Item ".\dist\aopmem-windows-x86_64\aopmem.exe" "$InstallDir\aopmem.exe" -Force
   101	& "$InstallDir\aopmem.exe" --version
   102	```
   103	
   104	Temp proof paths:
   105	
   106	- macOS: use `AOPMEM_HOME` with a temp path outside the target repo.
   107	- Windows PowerShell: use `$env:AOPMEM_HOME`, for example:
   108	
   109	```powershell
   110	$env:AOPMEM_HOME = "$env:TEMP\aopmem-proof"
   111	```
   112	
   113	Workspace rule:
   114	
   115	- Create or reuse the workspace under the selected AOPMem home:
   116	  `workspaces\<workspace-key>` on Windows and `workspaces/<workspace-key>` on
   117	  macOS.
   118	- Do not create `.aopmem` in the target repository.
   119	
   120	Ask only these 5 user-facing questions, exactly in this order:
   121	
   122	1. Включаем Understand Anything для локального понимания проекта и
   123	   .understand.docs?
   124	2. Включаем Codebase Memory MCP для навигации по коду?
   125	3. Объясни, что это за проект, зачем он нужен и чем мы тут занимаемся.
   126	4. Какая твоя роль в этом проекте и какая роль у агента?
   127	5. Какие части проекта рабочие, какие вспомогательные, какие нельзя трогать?
   128	
   129	Do not ask about:
   130	
   131	- OS
   132	- shell
   133	- repo path
   134	- workspace id
   135	- database location
   136	- adapter type
   137	- instruction file name
   138	- whether to use the default communication style
   139	- any long preferences/style questionnaire
   140	- any other technical facts you can detect silently
   141	
   142	After install:
   143	
   144	- briefly report what was done
   145	- report any optional setup that was skipped or failed in best-effort mode
   146	- confirm doctor result
   147	- do not dump unnecessary technical detail unless there is an error
   148	````
===== scripts/build_macos_arm.sh
     1	#!/usr/bin/env bash
     2	
     3	set -euo pipefail
     4	
     5	repo_root="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"
     6	cd "$repo_root"
     7	
     8	target_triple="aarch64-apple-darwin"
     9	dist_dir="$repo_root/dist/aopmem-darwin-arm64"
    10	dist_bin="$dist_dir/aopmem"
    11	
    12	host_triple="$(rustc -vV | awk '/^host: / { print $2 }')"
    13	
    14	if [[ "$host_triple" == "$target_triple" ]]; then
    15	  cargo build --release
    16	  built_bin="$repo_root/target/release/aopmem"
    17	else
    18	  cargo build --release --target "$target_triple"
    19	  built_bin="$repo_root/target/$target_triple/release/aopmem"
    20	fi
    21	
    22	if [[ ! -f "$built_bin" ]]; then
    23	  echo "missing built binary: $built_bin" >&2
    24	  exit 1
    25	fi
    26	
    27	mkdir -p "$dist_dir"
    28	cp "$built_bin" "$dist_bin"
    29	chmod 755 "$dist_bin"
    30	
    31	echo "built $dist_bin"
===== scripts/build_windows_x64_from_macos.sh
     1	#!/usr/bin/env bash
     2	
     3	set -euo pipefail
     4	
     5	repo_root="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"
     6	cd "$repo_root"
     7	
     8	target_triple="x86_64-pc-windows-msvc"
     9	rel_dist_bin="dist/aopmem-windows-x86_64/aopmem.exe"
    10	dist_dir="$repo_root/dist/aopmem-windows-x86_64"
    11	dist_bin="$dist_dir/aopmem.exe"
    12	built_bin="$repo_root/target/$target_triple/release/aopmem.exe"
    13	
    14	if [[ ! -f "$repo_root/Cargo.toml" ]]; then
    15	  echo "Cargo.toml not found at repo root: $repo_root" >&2
    16	  exit 1
    17	fi
    18	
    19	mkdir -p "$dist_dir"
    20	
    21	if cargo xwin --version >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    22	  rustup target add "$target_triple"
    23	  cargo xwin build --release --target "$target_triple"
    24	elif docker --version >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    25	  docker run --rm --platform linux/amd64 \
    26	    -v "$PWD":/io \
    27	    -w /io \
    28	    messense/cargo-xwin \
    29	    cargo xwin build --release --target "$target_triple"
    30	else
    31	  cat >&2 <<'EOF'
    32	BLOCKED_BUILD_ENV
    33	
    34	Install native cargo-xwin support, then rerun:
    35	
    36	brew install llvm
    37	cargo install --locked cargo-xwin
    38	rustup target add x86_64-pc-windows-msvc
    39	EOF
    40	  exit 1
    41	fi
    42	
    43	if [[ ! -s "$built_bin" ]]; then
    44	  echo "missing or empty built binary: $built_bin" >&2
    45	  exit 1
    46	fi
    47	
    48	cp "$built_bin" "$dist_bin"
    49	
    50	if [[ ! -s "$dist_bin" ]]; then
